ERROR
TypeError: Can't set immutable field x.
Note: Field is required to be mutable here:
let r = {x = 1; y = 2};
r.x <- 5
 ^~      
But the record is defined with that field immutable here:
// Should produce error about field not being mutable
let r = {x = 1; y = 2};
         ^              
r.x <- 5
Hint: To narrow down the cause of the type mismatch, consider adding an explicit type annotation here:
// Should produce error about field not being mutable
let r: _ = {x = 1; y = 2};
     +++                   
r.x <- 5
